>Function.prototype.toString()</code></a></li></ol></li><li><strong><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object\"><code>Object</code></a></strong></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Własności</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/constructor\"><code>Object.prototype.constructor</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/proto\"><code>Object.prototype.__proto__</code></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Metody</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p>Metoda <strong><code>Number.isNaN()</code></strong> określa czy podany parametr ma wartość <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> i czy jest typu <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a>. Jest to ulepszona wersja oryginalnej, globalne funkcji <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/isNaN\"><code>isNaN()</code></a>.</p>\n\n<div id=\"sect2\"><iframe class=\"interactive\" height=\"692\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/js/number-isnan.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"składnia","title":"Składnia","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\"><code>Number.isNaN(<var>value</var>)</code></pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parametry","title":"Parametry","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"value\"><code><var>value</var></code></dt>\n <dd>Wartość, którą będziemy testować <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a>.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"zwracana_wartość","title":"Zwracana wartość","isH3":true,"content":"<p><strong>true</strong>, jeśli podana wartość jest <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a>, a jej typem jest <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a>; w przeciwnym razie, <strong>false</strong>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"opis","title":"Opis","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Ponieważ oba operatory porównania, <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators\"><code>==</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> i <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators\"><code>===</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, dla zapytania czy <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> <em>jest równe</em> <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> zwracają <code>false</code> funkcja <code>Number.isNaN()</code> staje się niezbędna. Jest sytuacja wyjątkowa i nie występuje, gdy porównujemy dowolne inne wartości w języku JavaScript.</p>\n\n<p>W porównaniu do funkcji globalnej <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/isNaN\"><code>isNaN()</code></a>, metoda <code>Number.isNaN()</code> nie ma problemu z usilnym konwertowaniem parametru na liczbę. To oznacza, że można bezpiecznie przekazywać wartości, które normalnie mogłyby zostać skonwertowane na <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a>, ale nie mają tej samej wartości co <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a>. To również oznacza, że jedynie wartości typu <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a>, które są również <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a>, zwrócą <code>true</code>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"przykłady","title":"Przykłady","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>Number<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">NaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>        <span class=\"token comment\">// true</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>Number<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token number\">NaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// true</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>      <span class=\"token comment\">// true</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Gdybyśmy użyli funkcji isNaN(), te przykłady zwróciłby true</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'NaN'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>      <span class=\"token comment\">// false</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">undefined</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// false</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>         <span class=\"token comment\">// false</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'blabla'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>   <span class=\"token comment\">// false</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Wszystkie zwracają false</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">null</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">37</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'37'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'37.37'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">''</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nNumber<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isNaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">' '</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"polyfill","title":"Polyfill","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Następujący przykład działa, ponieważ <a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> jest jedyną wartością w języku JavaScript, która nie jest równa samej sobie.</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>Number<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>isNaN <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Number<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>isNaN <span class=\"token operator\">||</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">value</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> value <span class=\"token operator\">!==</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">null</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>value <span class=\"token operator\">!=</span> value <span class=\"token operator\">||</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span>value <span class=\"token operator\">!=</span> value<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"opis_2","title":"Opis","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Specification</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Comment</th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-number.isnan\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"pl\">The definition of 'Number.isnan' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Living Standard</span></td>\n   <td></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-number.isnan\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"pl\">The definition of 'Number.isnan' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initial definition.</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Kompatybilność","id":"kompatybilność","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.Number.isNaN","dataURL":"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isNaN/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect4\"></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"zobacz_również","title":"Zobacz również","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/isNaN\"><code>isNaN()</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Składnia","id":"składnia"},{"text":"Opis","id":"opis"},{"text":"Przykłady","id":"przykłady"},{"text":"Polyfill","id":"polyfill"},{"text":"Opis","id":"opis_2"},{"text":"Kompatybilność","id":"kompatybilność"},{"text":"Zobacz również","id":"zobacz_również"}],"summary":"Metoda Number.isNaN() określa czy podany parametr ma wartość NaN i czy jest typu Number. Jest to ulepszona wersja oryginalnej, globalne funkcji isNaN().","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Number.isNaN()","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch"},{"title":"Number.isNaN()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Number.isNaN()","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Number.isNaN()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Number.isNaN()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Number.isNaN()","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Number.isNaN()","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Number.isNaN()","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Number.isNaN()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"Number.isNaN()","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"pl/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/number/isnan","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/pl/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/number/isnan/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/pl/docs/Web","title":"Technologie Internetowe dla developerów"},{"uri":"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript","title":"JavaScript"},{"uri":"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference","title":"Dokumentacja referencyjna JavaScri